name: 3DMol.js
description: Structure 3D viewer, allowing proteins and ligands to be displayed and manipulated. Uses 3DMol.js from University of Pittsburgh

name: Atom Count (CXN)
description: Atom count calculator for structures using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: Box Plot
description: Displays data as a box plot using the D3 Javascript library

name: CNS MPO (CXN)
description: Multi-Parameter Optimisation score for drugs targeted at the Central Nervous Systmem (CNS).

name: CSV Upload
description: Allows a text file to be uploaded into the system. Comma and tab separated formats are supported along with basic options like whether to handle first line as headers.

name: Canonical Smiles (RDKit)
description: Generate a canonical smiles string for structures using RDKit

name: ChEMBL Activities Fetcher
description: Pulls compound and activity data  for a specified assay ID from the ChEMBL REST web services at the EBI

name: Chemcentral Similarity Search
description: Search our "house" databases using similarity search

name: Chemcentral Structure Search
description: Search our "house" databases using exact or substructure search

name: Chemcentral multi-search
description: Search our "house" databases to find structures similar to any of the input structures

name: Convert to Molecules
description: Generate molecules from text representation e.g. a smiles column from a CSV file

name: Dataset Docker Processor
description: Process a dataset using a specified Docker container

name: Dataset Enricher
description: Enriches one dataset with content from another

name: Dataset Potion
description: A simple language for performing powerful data transformations

name: Dataset Random Selector
description: Select records at random from a dataset

name: Dataset UUID filter
description: Filter a dataset with a set of UUIDs

name: Dataset slice selector
description: Simple cell that let's you prepare a subset of a large dataset starting at a specified entry and including a specified number of entry

name: Dataset sorter
description: Sort a dataset by one or more fields

name: Drug-like Filter (CXN)
description: Apply a drug likeness filter to molecules using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: ECFP4 Screen (CXN)
description: Filter molecules with ECFP fingerprints similarity using ChemAxon's Screen

name: Formal Charge (RDKit)
description: Calculates the formal charge of a molecule. e.g. 1+, 2+, 1-, 0 (for neutral)

name: Frac sp3 C (RDKit)
description: Calculate the fraction of sp3 hybridised carbon atoms for structures using RDKit

name: Ghose filter (CXN)
description: Ghose drug like filter implemented with ChemAxon's property calculators

name: Ghose filter (RDKit)
description: Ghose drug like filter implemented using RDKit

name: Groovy Dataset Filter
description: Filter a dataset based on an expression using the Groovy programming language.

name: HBA & HBD (CDK)
description: H-bond acceptors and donors using Chemistry Development Kit

name: HBA & HBD (RDKit)
description: Calculate the number of h-bond donors and acceptors for structures using RDKit

name: Heatmap
description: Display of relationships between data using a heatmap

name: Image Viewer
description: Simple viewer for image files

name: KiDS MPO (CXN)
description: Multi-Parameter Optimisation score for kinase drugs.

name: Lipinski filter (CXN)
description: Lipinski filter for structures using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: Lipinski filter (RDKIT)
description: Calculate Lipinski properties for structures using RDKit

name: LogD (CXN)
description: LogD predictor for structures using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: LogP (CDK)
description: ALogP and XLogP predictors for structures using Chemistry Development Kit

name: LogP (CXN)
description: LogP predictor for structures using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: LogP (OpenChemLib)
description: LogP predictor for structures using OpenChemLib

name: LogP (RDKit)
description: Predict LogP using RDKit

name: LogS (CXN)
description: LogS (solubility) predictor for structures using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: LogS (OpenChemLib)
description: Solubility (LogS) predictor for structures using OpenChemLib

name: Merge Datasets
description: Merge multiple datasets into one using a common key. Useful for combining data from multiple sources into a single dataset where there is a common identifier linking the records

name: MolAlignAssemblies
description: Alignment of 3D structures

name: Molar Refractivity (RDKit)
description: Predict molar refractivity using RDKit

name: Molecule standardisers
description: Two cells performing molecular standardisation using the MolVS and Flatkinson standardisers.

name: MoleculeEnumerator
description: Enumerates potential variants of a structure using RDKit

name: Molecules From Field
description: Creates a new dataset containing molecules present in the specified field of the input.

name: Molfile Upload
description: Allows a dataset to be created from a file in molfile format. The dataset will contain a single structure.

name: NGL Viewer
description: NGL 3D viewer from Alexander Rose

name: PAINS filter (RDKit)
description: Filter molecules using PAINS (Pan Assay Interference Compounds) filters, implemented with RDKit

name: PDB Upload
description: Allows  file in PDB format to be uploaded

name: PLI score
description: Scores docked structures using the Astex PLI scoring algorithm.

name: PSA (OpenChemLib)
description: Calculate the polar surface area for structures using OpenChemLib

name: Parallel Coordinate Plot
description: Display and filter data using a parallel coordinate plot

name: Pharmacophore Screen (CXN)
description: Filter molecules with a 2D pharmacophore similarity using ChemAxon's Screen

name: RDKit Butina Clustering
description: Cluster molecules using the Butina algorithm from RDKit.

name: RDKit Cluster Matrix
description: Generates a clustered distance matrix from a dataset of molecules using Butina clustering from RDKit.

name: RDKit Conformers
description: Generate 3D conformers of molecules using RDKit

name: RDKit Constrained Conformers
description: Generate conformers of a molecule, constraining a part of a molecule to fixed coordinates.

name: RDKit Diverse Subset Picker
description: Cluster molecules using the Butina algorithm from RDKit and then pick a diverse subset of the molecules

name: RDKit MaxMin Picker
description: Picks diverse subset of compounds using the MaxMinPicker algorithm as implemented in RDKit

name: RDKit Multi-Similarity Screening
description: Virtual screening using molecular similarity

name: RDKit Open3D Align
description: Performs 3D alignment of molecules using Open3DAlign

name: RDKit Similarity Screening
description: Virtual screening using molecular similarity

name: REOS Filter (RDKit)
description: Rapid Elimination Of Swill filter - a drug-like structure filter using RDKit

name: REOS filter (CXN)
description: Apply a drug likeness filter to molecules using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: Ring Count (RDKit)
description: Calculate the number of rings and aromatic rings for structures using RDKit

name: Rotatable bonds (RDKit)
description: Calculate the number of rotatable rings for structures using RDKit

name: Rule of 3 filter (CXN)
description: Astex rule of 3 filter for filtering fragment libraries implemented with ChemAxon

name: Rule of 3 filter (RDKit)
description: Astex rule of 3 filter for filtering fragment libraries implemented with RDKit

name: SDF Export (CDK)
description: Export structures to SDF using Chemistry Development Kit

name: SDF Upload
description: Allows a MDL SD file to be uploaded into the system. Structures and data are handled.

name: SMARTCyp
description: SMARTCyp metabolic site prediction

name: SMoG2016
description: Scores docked structures using the SMoG 2016 scoring algorithm.

name: Scatter Plot
description: Displays data as a scatter plot using the D3 Javascript library

name: Smiles Structures
description: Read structures from smiles strings

name: Smiles deduplicator
description: De-duplicate a set of structures using a canonical smiles field

name: SphereEx Clustering (CXN)
description: Cluster molecules using sphere exclusion clustering and ECFP fingerprints using ChemAxon's JKulstor

name: TPSA (RDKit)
description: Calculate topological polar surface area for structures using RDKit

name: Table Display
description: Displays data as a familiar table/spreadsheet

name: Tmax Cmax Simulation
description: Simulator for Pharmacokinetic profiling of a compound

name: Transform Values
description: Convert data types e.g. convert from text to numbers

name: Trusted Groovy Script
description: Process a dataset using a Groovy script. The script is trusted and executed "in process"

name: Untrusted Groovy Script
description: Process a dataset using a Groovy script. The script is not trusted and executed in its own safe sandbox.

name: Veber filter (CXN)
description: Veber filter for orally active drugs implemented using ChemAxon

name: Veber filter (RDKit)
description: Veber filter for orally active drugs implemented using RDKit

name: Verify structure (CDK)
description: Verify that the molecules are valid according to CDK

name: Verify structure (CXN)
description: Verify that the molecules are valid according to ChemAxon's Marvin

name: Verify structure (OCL)
description: Verify that the molecules are valid according to OpenChemLib

name: Verify structure (RDKit)
description: Verify that the molecules are valid according to RDKit

name: Wiener Numbers (CDK)
description: Wiener path and polarity numbers using Chemistry Development Kit

name: XChem Reaction Maker
description: Enumerate input molecules using a specified reaction and some reactions

name: XChem Reaction Smarts Filter
description: Filter a set of molecules according to whether they contain a substructure fragment compatible with a set of reaction types

name: ZipFileUpload
description: Cell that allows a zip file to be uploaded.

name: pKa (CXN)
description: Acidic and basic pKa predictors using ChemAxon's property calculators

name: rDock Docking
description: Ligand docking using rDock
